or the fruit to release its flavour.</p><p>Avoid overcooking them, or they will turn too mushy.</p>\n								<img width=\"814\" height=\"750\" src=\"http://localhost/a/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/vg-blog-img-step-3-opt.jpg\" alt=\"\" />					\n								<img width=\"814\" height=\"750\" src=\"http://localhost/a/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/vg-blog-img-step-3-opt.jpg\" alt=\"\" />					\n				<h4>Step 4</h4> \n			<p>Now, tip in the king prawns and squeeze in the lime.</p><p>Cook the banana curry for a further 5 minutes.</p><p>When the shrimps turn pink and slightly curved, they’re ready. Avoid overcooking them, or they will shrink too much and get chewy.</p><p>To finish, serve this delicious prawn banana curry with steamed rice and garnish with black pepper and thyme.</p>', 'Vegan Ube Mochi Waffles', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vegan-ube-mochi-waffles', '', '', '2024-02-27 15:00:00', '2024-02-27 15:00:00', '', 0, 'https://dummy.xtemos.com/woodmart2/vegetables-elementor/?p=960', 0, 'post', '', 0),
